# Job Finding Agent

This branch is the clean rebuild branch.

- Frozen prototype: `v0-prototype`
- Frozen tag: `v0`
- Current rebuild branch: `v1-rebuild`

The goal of this branch is to rebuild the project in a more controlled way:

- define the system in small reviewed steps
- implement one slice at a time
- keep input/output logs inside the project
- keep the codebase minimal and explicit

Current repo state:

- `app/`: application code
- `config/`: runtime config
- `prompts/`: future prompt files
- `scripts/`: runnable entrypoints
- `tests/`: test suite
- `data/logs/`: runtime logs
- `data/job_finding.sqlite3`: runtime database
- `docs/`: design docs for the rebuild

LinkedIn rebuild structure:

- `docs/linkedin/`: step docs and user instructions
- `app/linkedin/`: LinkedIn-specific code
- `scripts/linkedin/`: stage runners
- `config/app.yaml`: global runtime config

Start from:

- [docs/01-project-phases.md](docs/01-project-phases.md)
- [docs/02-linkedin-slice.md](docs/02-linkedin-slice.md)
- [docs/03-logging-contract.md](docs/03-logging-contract.md)
- [docs/linkedin/00-linkedin-sources.md](docs/linkedin/00-linkedin-sources.md)
- [docs/linkedin/01-step0-connection.md](docs/linkedin/01-step0-connection.md)

Current LinkedIn pipeline:

1. browser connection check
2. browser source ingestion
   - keyword search
   - recommended feed
3. email source ingestion
4. title triage
5. detail fetch
6. JD enrichment
7. ranking
8. Easy Apply assistant (separate no-submit runner)

Current persistence design:

- stage logs under `data/logs/`
- direct writes to SQLite
- no intermediate runtime artifacts

Current job lifecycle:

- `discovered`
- `triaged`
- `detailed`
- `enriched`
- `not_applicable`

Current LLM stage docs:

- [docs/linkedin/llm/title-triage.md](docs/linkedin/llm/title-triage.md)
- [docs/linkedin/llm/jd-enrichment.md](docs/linkedin/llm/jd-enrichment.md)
- [docs/linkedin/llm/ranking.md](docs/linkedin/llm/ranking.md)

Current application-assistant doc:

- [docs/linkedin/06-easy-apply-assistant.md](docs/linkedin/06-easy-apply-assistant.md)
